# Console simples com observabilidade

## 1) Objetivo
Padronizar apps console focados em processos batch simples, com logging estruturado e tracing.

## 2) Estrutura de pastas
```
src/
  App/
    Program.cs
    Jobs/
  Application/
    Services/
  Infrastructure/
    Observability/
deploy/
  Dockerfile
tests/
  Unit/
```

## 3) Pacotes recomendados
- Serilog.Extensions.Hosting, Serilog.Sinks.Console
- OpenTelemetry.Extensions.Hosting
- OpenTelemetry.Instrumentation.Http
- OpenTelemetry.Exporter.OpenTelemetryProtocol
- MediatR (para orquestrar jobs/comandos)

## 4) Configuracao (Program.cs)
```csharp
using Microsoft.Extensions.Hosting;
using Serilog;
using OpenTelemetry.Trace;

Host.CreateDefaultBuilder(args)
    .UseSerilog((ctx, cfg) => cfg.ReadFrom.Configuration(ctx.Configuration))
    .ConfigureServices((ctx, services) =>
    {
        services.AddMediatR(cfg => cfg.RegisterServicesFromAssemblyContaining<Program>());
        services.AddOpenTelemetry()
            .WithTracing(t => t.AddHttpClientInstrumentation().AddSource("BatchJobs"));
        services.AddHostedService<ImportJob>();
    })
    .Build()
    .Run();
```

## 5) Exemplo de Job
```csharp
public class ImportJob : BackgroundService
{
    private readonly ILogger<ImportJob> _logger;
    public ImportJob(ILogger<ImportJob> logger) => _logger = logger;

    protected override async Task ExecuteAsync(CancellationToken stoppingToken)
    {
        _logger.LogInformation("Import job started");
        // processamento aqui
        await Task.Delay(TimeSpan.FromSeconds(1), stoppingToken);
        _logger.LogInformation("Import job finished");
    }
}
```

## 6) Observabilidade
- Logs estruturados com Serilog.
- Tracing de chamadas HTTP (quando existirem) e spans manuais para etapas do job.

## 7) Dockerfile (opcional)
```Dockerfile
FROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/runtime:9.0 AS base
WORKDIR /app

FROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:9.0 AS build
WORKDIR /src
COPY . .
RUN dotnet restore ./src/App/App.csproj
RUN dotnet publish ./src/App/App.csproj -c Release -o /app/publish

FROM base AS final
WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=build /app/publish .
ENTRYPOINT ["dotnet", "App.dll"]
```

## 8) Testes
- Unit: services e orquestradores dos jobs.
- Smoke: execucao do binario validando codigo de saida.

## 9) Checklist
- Observabilidade ativa (logs + traces quando aplicavel).
- Job principal coberto por testes unitarios.
- Dockerfile pronto se necessitar conteinerizacao.
